    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available is a mechanically sound 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six power plant with individual throttle bodies. This example is equipped with the desirable Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox, providing direct engagement and precise shifts. The chassis dynamics are sharpened by a variable M differential lock and a refreshed suspension setup featuring upgraded bushings for improved turn-in response. Crucial preventative maintenance has been proactively addressed, including a reinforced rear subframe and a comprehensive VANOS overhaul to ensure optimal variable valve timing across the power band. While the exterior displays minor road-derived patina consistent with a well-loved driver, the drivetrain remains potent, pulling linearly to the 8,000 RPM redline. This is a driver-focused machine optimized for heel-and-toe downshifts and balanced cornering.",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.4,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 25
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_3_listing_3",
      "firm_id": "sybil_3",
